**v20 Server-Side Speaker-Count Routing + Stall Reset (June 2026):**
- `compose-clip-webhook` previously *always* invoked `compose-dialog-segments` (v5) after the cinematic-sync master plate finished — including for 3+ speaker scenes where v5's multi-pass chain reproducibly returns Sync.so "An unknown error occurred." (diffusion model rejects its own re-encoded output). The client `useTwoShotAutoTrigger` then auto-retried with v4, succeeding — but burning one v5 attempt + 81-credit refund + flashing a false "Fehler" banner first.
- v20 mirrors the client's routing inside the webhook: compute `speakerCount` from `audio_plan.speakers` / `audio_plan.twoshot.speakers` / unique `character_id` in segments. If `>= 3` (or `engine_override === 'cinematic-sync-legacy'`), invoke `compose-dialog-scene` (v4 per-turn) directly. Otherwise keep v5. Also gates the auto-invoke on `lip_sync_status !== 'canceled'` so a fresh user cancel can't be revived by a late master-plate webhook.
- `usePipelineProgress`:
  - `lipsyncReal.failed` now ignores scenes whose `clip_error` starts with `auto-retry:` while `lipSyncStatus !== 'failed'` — recovering scenes shouldn't drive the bar red.
  - A new `lipsyncFailedRef` effect resets `realProgressRef`, `runFloorRef` and `floorRef.lipsync` when lipsync transitions from `failed → not-failed`. Without this, the 4-min stall detector kept `hasFailure=true` after auto-recovery because the prior v5 attempt had already pushed `runFloorRef` past 90% with no real progress for >4 min.
- `cancel-dialog-lipsync` now collects job ids from BOTH `dialog_shots.shots[*].sync_job_id` (v4) AND `audio_plan.twoshot.syncJobs.jobs[]` (v5) AND `replicate_prediction_id` (`sync:<id>`), dedupes, then issues `DELETE https://api.sync.so/v2/generations/<id>` for each (best-effort, requires `SYNC_SO_API_KEY`). Stops Sync.so billing on cancel.
- SceneCard "✕ Lip-Sync abbrechen" button is now also visible during the brief `lip_sync_status === 'failed'` window so the user can opt out of the auto-retry loop entirely.

**v19 Visible-Lipsync + Stable-Plate (June 2026):**
- `sync-so-webhook` (v4 per-turn path) now downloads the Sync.so result (`https://api.sync.so/v2/generations/<id>/result?token=…`) and re-uploads it to `ai-videos/composer/<uid>/<sceneId>-dialog-turn-<idx>.mp4`, persisting the stable public URL in `shot.output_url` (+ flag `output_url_rehosted`). Without this, Remotion Lambda failed to load the auth-token-protected sync.so URL during DialogStitchVideo and silently fell back to the muted master plate — the stitched clip showed no lip motion at all. Mirrors the v5 multi-pass re-host that already existed.
- `compose-dialog-scene` now appends `buildDialogPlatePromptSuffix(speakerCount)` to the master plate prompt whenever the cinematic-sync dialog hotfix re-renders the Hailuo master: locked-off framing, head-and-shoulders, no handheld/dolly/orbit, no waving hands, no head turn away, no exaggerated gestures. Fixes the "noodle limb" body motion that no lipsync can rescue.
- SceneCard "🔁 Lip-Sync neu rendern" button additionally clears `clip_url / clip_status / reference_image_url / lip_sync_source_clip_url / lip_sync_applied_at` so the hotfix branch fires every time the user manually re-rolls a cinematic-sync dialog scene, guaranteeing the constrained prompt is used.



**v18 Cancel-Pfad (User-initiierter Abbruch):**
- Neue Edge Function `cancel-dialog-lipsync` (verify_jwt via getClaims): auth-prüft Project-Owner, holt Dialog-Lock, löscht alle `sync_job_id`s aus `syncso_inflight_jobs`, setzt `dialog_shots.status='canceled'` (+ `canceled_at`, `canceled_by`), `lip_sync_status='canceled'`, `twoshot_stage=null`, `clip_error='lipsync_canceled_by_user'`. Optional `reset:true` setzt zusätzlich `dialog_shots=null` für sauberen Neustart.
- `poll-dialog-shots/processSceneLocked` returnt sofort `status='canceled'` wenn `lip_sync_status==='canceled'` ODER `dialog_shots.status==='canceled'` → keine neuen Preclip/Sync.so/Stitch-Dispatches mehr.
- `sync-so-webhook` (v4-Pfad) returnt 200 mit `skipped:'canceled'` wenn die Szene cancelled ist → kein Retry, kein Degrade, kein State-Overwrite.
- `remotion-webhook` (`dialog-turn-preclip` UND `dialog-stitch` Branches): innerhalb des Dialog-Locks Cancel-State erkennen und das Schreiben von `preclip_url`/`clip_url`/`lip_sync_applied_at` skippen → späte Lambda-Renderings können den Abbruch nicht aufheben.
- `useTwoShotAutoTrigger` Candidate-Filter ignoriert `lip_sync_status==='canceled'` komplett → kein Auto-Retry. Explizites "Lip-Sync neu rendern" bleibt der einzige Wiedereinstieg.
- UI: SceneCard zeigt während `running/stitching/audio_muxing/pending` oder aktiver `twoshot_stage` den Button "✕ Lip-Sync abbrechen". Optimistic local update + invoke('cancel-dialog-lipsync', { reset: true }).

**v18 Integrity-Guard Korrektur (kompatibel mit v17 Preclip = Auto-Speaker):**
- Alte Regel verlangte für Multi-Speaker-Szenen pro Shot `target_coords && deterministic_coords === true`. Das kollidierte mit v17, wo Preclips bewusst mit `auto_detect:true` ohne Koordinaten dispatched werden.
- Neue Regel akzeptiert pro Shot EINEN der beiden deterministischen Pfade:
  - `sync_source_kind === 'preclip' && !!preclip_url` → Single-Face-Crop, Auto-Speaker ist deterministisch
  - `sync_source_kind === 'master' && target_coords && deterministic_coords === true` → Wide-Plate mit fixen Koordinaten
- Sonst: terminal failed + Refund + `clip_error='lipsync_wrong_face_guard'`.

**v17 Preclip = Auto-Speaker (Artlist-Parität):**
- In `poll-dialog-shots` wird bei `usePreclip === true` der Dispatch-Modus IMMER auf `auto` gezwungen. Sync.so bekommt **keine** `coordinates` + `frame_number` mehr, sondern `active_speaker_detection: { auto_detect: true }`.
- Begründung: Preclips sind isolierte Single-Face-Clips, in denen Wide-Plate-Koordinaten aus dem Master keine Bedeutung haben. Die alten Coords lösten reproduzierbar `An unknown error occurred.` für Edge-Faces in 3-Sprecher-Plates aus.
- Coords + frame_number bleiben ausschließlich für den Master-Legacy-Pfad (`sync_source_kind === 'master'`).
- Face-Gate wird für Preclips dadurch automatisch übersprungen (Gate ist `mode === 'coords'`-gated).

**v17 VAD relaxed für kurze Turns:**
- Alte Regel blockte "Was denn?" (voicedRatio=42%, longestRun=0.30s) als `preflight_audio_no_voice`.
- Neue Regel: wenn `voicedRatio >= 0.35`, reicht `longestVoicedRun >= 0.15s`. Bei niedrigerer Dichte gilt weiterhin `longestVoicedRun >= 0.4s`. Wirklich silent (< 0.15 ratio) wird unverändert geblockt.

**v17 sync-so-webhook v4 Degrade nur noch ≤2 Sprecher:**
- Wenn die Webhook-Retry-Matrix erschöpft ist, wird für `speakerCount >= 3` der Shot terminal `failed` markiert (kein `ready+degraded`). Für 1/2 Sprecher bleibt der sichere Degrade-auf-Master-Plate-Pfad aktiv.

**Per-scene dispatch lock (v15+v16):**
- `dialog_dispatch_locks(scene_id PK, holder, acquired_at, expires_at)` mit SECURITY DEFINER RPCs `try_acquire_dialog_lock` / `release_dialog_lock`. Shared helper `_shared/dialog-lock.ts` → `withDialogLock(...)`.
- ALLE read-modify-write von `dialog_shots` laufen im Lock: poll-dialog-shots/processScene, remotion-webhook (dialog-turn-preclip + dialog-stitch), sync-so-webhook v4 per-turn patch, cancel-dialog-lipsync.

**v16 Reconciliation Step 0 + Hard-forbid Master-Fallback für ≥3 Sprecher** bleiben aktiv (siehe Code in `poll-dialog-shots`).

**Bestätigte erfolgreiche 3-Sprecher-Pipeline (Lauf 699e85ff…):**
- 3× Preclip via Remotion Lambda → 3× Sync.so dispatch mit `mode=auto` → 3× ready → Lambda DialogStitchVideo Stitch → `lip_sync_status='done'`, `final_url` gesetzt. Bestätigt v17-Preclip-Pfad + v16-Lock + v18-Integrity-Guard.

